The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 NIIT Global acquires North American firm

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Thadani: Buyout mode

 Mumbai, July 27: NIIT Global, the Delhi-based IT training company, has acquired North Americas Element K, a learning software provider for an undisclosed sum. The transaction is expected to close within two weeks. 

 When the deal goes through, the merged entity will have more than 3,000 employees, over $250 million in revenues and a presence in 32 countries. 

 This acquisition is consistent with our stated plans for accelerated growth in developed economies, said Vijay Thadani, CEO of NIIT.

 Element K has an established base of highly satisfied clients in the United States and Canada, and is a well respected brand in the training industry. They are moving successfully into the North American Learning BPO marketplace and will benefit from NIITs global presence and complementary learning services, he added. 

 NIIT Limited has reported a 33 per cent growth in revenue year-on-year. The company reported corporate business growth at 17 per cent for the same period. 

 NIIT has reported a net consolidated revenue of Rs 110.2 crore this quarter compared with Rs 106.4 crore in the corresponding previous period. The companys global system-wide revenues stood at Rs 163.7 crore compared with Rs 156.6 crore in the first quarter of 2005-06. The company has recorded an operating profit of Rs 15.4 crore compared with Rs 14.3 crore last year. Net profit at Rs 13.2 crore during the quarter led to a basic earning per share of Rs 6.8, the company said. 




